race.comment: FACEOFF (5) disappointed first-up at Kembla Grange but rates highly off his form last campaign. His trials coming in had been solid and he'll be better suited coming back to Country level. Bouldvillain sticks with the gelding, and if he can sit closer today he'll be very hard to beat. LONDON STAR (7) has trialled well in readiness for her this. She won her maiden impressively two back before tackling Provincial company before the break. The sting out of the ground is a big tick for her and she'll be flying late in the race. BOOM IN THE DARK (6) got the job done here in deteriorating conditions, sitting back and launching late to score over 1010m. Out in trip should suit him better and Heywood sticking is a positive sign. Can repeat the dose. MERCHANT REIGN (8) will find this a bit easier today third-up and can be in the finish. LIGHTLY SPARKLED (11) needs some luck from the draw but looks poised to strike third-up and with the blinkers on first time.
